    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-03-18T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-03-18T00:00:00-05:00" n="1518"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1518">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.41/197.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to Special
                        Agent <persName type="to">Carothers</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-03-18">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 18, 1914</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>We have received information to the effect that the incidents connected with the
                    Benton case have increased any prejudice that Villa may have had against British
                    subjects of northern Mexico and alarm is felt lest he may commit or permit harsh
                    treatment of them. As you will be near him please bear this danger in mind and
                    use your influence to prevent any improper acts on Villa’s part or failure to
                    give that protection to British subjects and other foreigners which he and
                    Carranza have repeatedly promised.</p>
                <p>It would embarrass us and greatly injure the Constitutionalist cause if anything
                    were done that could arouse abroad additional criticism of Constitutionalist
                    methods.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
